---
import "./services.css";
import Layout from "$/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Our services" description="Useful AI implementation, enterprise architecture and governance, and technical education from Stackific.">
  <main id="main">
    <section class="container-xl mt-9 m:mt-10 p-1 m:p-2 l:p-5" aria-labelledby="services-heading">
      <h1 id="services-heading" class="text-6 m:text-7 lh--1 fw-7">Our services</h1>
      <p class="text-2 m:text-3 mt-3 svc-lede">
        Three ways we work with organizations serious about building AI well.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="container-xl mt-8 m:mt-10 p-1 m:p-2 l:p-5" aria-labelledby="svc-implement-heading">
      <article class="no-elevate round p-5 svc-card">
        <div class="p-3 m:p-5">
          <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-eyebrow">01 — Engineering</p>
          <h2 id="svc-implement-heading" class="text-5 m:text-6 lh-2 fw-7 mt-2">Useful AI Implementation</h2>
          <p class="text-2 m:text-3 fw-4 mt-2 svc-sub">For organizations ready to move from idea to working system.</p>

          <div class="grid mt-7">
            <div class="s12 m12 l8">
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-0">
                You know AI could be valuable. You may even know where. But the gap between "this could work" and "this works" is where most efforts stall.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                We close that gap. We work alongside your team to design, build, and ship AI capabilities that solve real problems in your specific context. Not a demo. Not a proof of concept destined for a shelf. Working systems that your people actually use and that deliver measurable outcomes.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                This is hands-on engineering: we write code, we architect systems, we iterate with your team until the solution is sound and sustainable. We transfer knowledge as we go, so you are never dependent on us to maintain what we built together.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="s12 m12 l4">
              <article class="no-elevate round p-4 svc-fit">
                <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-fit-label">Best suited for</p>
                <p class="text-1 mt-2">
                  Startups and growing companies making their first serious AI investments, or teams that have experimented but need engineering rigor to move from prototype to production.
                </p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="container-xl mt-8 m:mt-10 p-1 m:p-2 l:p-5" aria-labelledby="svc-architecture-heading">
      <article class="no-elevate round p-5 svc-card">
        <div class="p-3 m:p-5">
          <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-eyebrow">02 — Advisory</p>
          <h2 id="svc-architecture-heading" class="text-5 m:text-6 lh-2 fw-7 mt-2">Enterprise AI Architecture and Governance</h2>
          <p class="text-2 m:text-3 fw-4 mt-2 svc-sub">For organizations navigating AI at scale.</p>

          <div class="grid mt-7">
            <div class="s12 m12 l8">
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-0">
                Adopting AI across a large organization is not primarily a technical challenge. It is an architectural one, a policy one, and ultimately a cultural one. The decisions you make now about governance, infrastructure, and principles will shape what your organization is capable of for years.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                We advise at the level where those decisions are made. We help leadership and engineering teams define AI strategies grounded in your actual capabilities and constraints. We design architectures that are reliable, auditable, and aligned with your values. We help draft policies that are principled and practical, not just compliant.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                We bring the perspective of people who have led engineering organizations at scale and who understand that the hardest problems are never purely technical.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="s12 m12 l4">
              <article class="no-elevate round p-4 svc-fit">
                <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-fit-label">Best suited for</p>
                <p class="text-1 mt-2">
                  Enterprises and larger organizations establishing or refining their AI strategy, governance, or technical architecture.
                </p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="container-xl mt-8 m:mt-10 p-1 m:p-2 l:p-5" aria-labelledby="svc-stackdemy-heading">
      <article class="no-elevate round p-5 svc-card">
        <div class="p-3 m:p-5">
          <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-eyebrow">03 — Education</p>
          <h2 id="svc-stackdemy-heading" class="text-5 m:text-6 lh-2 fw-7 mt-2">Technical Education: Stackdemy</h2>
          <p class="text-2 m:text-3 fw-4 mt-2 svc-sub">For senior practitioners who want depth, not hype.</p>

          <div class="grid mt-7">
            <div class="s12 m12 l8">
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-0">
                Most AI education is aimed at beginners or pitched as inspiration for executives. There is very little for the experienced engineer or technical leader who wants to genuinely understand what is happening at the frontier and how to apply it with skill.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                Stackdemy exists because we build before we teach. Every course on the platform comes from real findings: techniques we refined on production systems, architectural patterns we discovered solving hard problems for clients, and better ways to engineer that emerged from doing the work. We do not teach theory we read about. We share what we have tested, applied, and proven.
              </p>
              <p class="text-1 m:text-2 mt-3">
                This is not a library of introductory tutorials. It is a focused curriculum for people who already know how to build and want to build better.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="s12 m12 l4">
              <article class="no-elevate round p-4 svc-fit">
                <p class="text-0 fw-6 svc-fit-label">Best suited for</p>
                <p class="text-1 mt-2">
                  Senior engineers, engineering managers, and technical leaders across organizations of any size.
                </p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="container-xl mt-9 m:mt-10 mb-10 p-1 m:p-2 l:p-5" aria-labelledby="svc-cta-heading">
      <article class="no-elevate round middle-align p-5 secondary-container">
        <div class="p-3 m:p-5">
          <h2 id="svc-cta-heading" class="text-4 lh-2 fw-7">Not sure which fits?</h2>
          <p class="text-2 mt-3">Tell us what you are trying to build. We will listen carefully and tell you honestly whether we can help.</p>
          <button type="button" data-ui="#contact-dialog" class="h-8 w-12 text-1 l:text-2 mt-3">Work with us</button>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
